                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-29T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 29, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12 noon.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. Department’s telegram No. 27, September 27, 6 p.m.<note n="35"
                        xml:id="d320fn35">See footnote 33, <ref target="#pg_359">p.
                        359</ref>.</note> At noon today I conveyed the message as desired to the
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs. He expressed his Government’s appreciation of the
                    friendly interest manifested by the United States and promised a more responsive
                    answer after the message had been duly considered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
